' Episode 4 Recap And Review: The 'Star Wars' We Were Looking For |work=[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2019/11/29/the-mandalorian-episode-4-review-this-is-the-star-wars-we-were-waiting-for/ |accessdate=February 19, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126024312/https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2019/11/29/the-mandalorian-episode-4-review-this-is-the-star-wars-we-were-waiting-for/ |archive-date=January 26, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Young |first=Bryan |title='The Mandalorian' Goes Full 'Seven Samurai' With \"Sanctuary\" |work=[[/Film]] |date=November 29, 2019 |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/the-mandalorian-sanctuary-review/ |accessdate=February 19, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222052125/https://www.slashfilm.com/the-mandalorian-sanctuary-review/ |archive-date=December 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Atkin |first=Jesse |title=5 Reasons The Witcher Geralt Will Be a Better Dad Than the Mandalorian (& 5 Reasons He Won't) |work=[[Screen Rant]] |date=December 30, 2019 |url=https://screenrant.com/5-reasons-the-witcher-geralt-will-be-a-better-dad-than-the-mandalorian-5-reasons-he-wont/ |accessdate=February 19, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200220043947/https://screenrant.com/5-reasons-the-witcher-geralt-will-be-a-better-dad-than-the-mandalorian-5-reasons-he-wont/ |archive-date=February 20, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The Mandalorian and the Child visit the planet [[Tatooine]] in \"[[Chapter 5: The Gunslinger]]\", during which the Mandalorian leaves the Child in the care of a mechanic named [[Peli Motto]] ([[Amy Sedaris]]). The Child and Peli are briefly abducted by a bounty hunter named [[Toro Calican]] ([[Jake Cannavale]]), whom the Mandalorian kills.<ref name=\"Keane1207\">{{cite news |last=Keane |first=Sean |title=The Mandalorian episode 5 recap: Baby Yoda travels to an iconic planet |work=[[CNET]] 